		<td><b>Question regarding open-bus read</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just a quick silly question: when reading an open-bus data location with the 2A03 or the 6510 or alike, it reads back the last byte that was on the bus, and I'm wondering if this is due to the capacitance of the bus or it is due to active bus holders?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
